race.comment: DOUBTING EYE (6) returned from a break and drifted back before closing powerfully to score over 1050m at Rockhampton. He's further improved and has placed 3/5 second-up. Carries just 1k more and stripping fitter he can take the next step. MASTER MONTARO (1) spiked his figures just missing in that contest. He led them up and just has to hold the form to threaten. FLYING SHAMUS (7) found more like her best narrowly beaten at Mackay. Comes back to a shorter sprint off a 33-day freshen and the in-form Olzard is engaged. Sits down in the weights and has claims. SOOPAT (4) is also a hope building on his easy win at Mt Isa. A 2kg apprentice allowance assists today.
